1
00:00:32,659 --> 00:00:33,952
Hey!

2
00:00:35,120 --> 00:00:36,788
How long have I...

3
00:00:37,247 --> 00:00:39,916
Blunt force trauma to the head did
the fatal damage.

4
00:00:40,041 --> 00:00:41,761
Since the accident,
he's had a continuous...

5
00:00:41,918 --> 00:00:45,547
Can't get up.
What's wrong with my legs?

6
00:00:46,589 --> 00:00:49,342
Hey, someone talk to me!

7
00:00:49,884 --> 00:00:52,220
Hey, you don't hear me
talking to you?

8
00:00:57,350 --> 00:00:58,685
Great heart for transplant.

9
00:00:58,810 --> 00:00:59,769
Who?

10
00:01:00,103 --> 00:01:03,606
My heart? Oh, God.
They don't know I'm in here.

11
00:01:03,732 --> 00:01:08,069
Hey, genius. I think it violates
certain ethical laws

12
00:01:08,278 --> 00:01:10,447
to rip the organs out of a guy
that's still alive.

13
00:01:10,697 --> 00:01:12,157
Possibly certain law laws, too.

14
00:01:12,282 --> 00:01:13,241
Thank you.

15
00:01:13,366 --> 00:01:16,494
Could you get back
in your bed, please, Mr. House?

16
00:01:16,619 --> 00:01:17,579
It's actually Dr. House.

17
00:01:17,704 --> 00:01:18,663
This guy's a doctor?

18
00:01:18,788 --> 00:01:20,749
There's also a Navy SEAL House,

19
00:01:20,874 --> 00:01:22,125
but you're gonna
have to save up for that one.

20
00:01:22,250 --> 00:01:24,544
Really? Well,
that's interesting,

21
00:01:24,669 --> 00:01:26,129
but you're here because
you crashed your motorcycle,

22
00:01:26,254 --> 00:01:29,340
not because I need
a consult, so get back in bed.

23
00:01:29,507 --> 00:01:32,051
Scraped my elbow.
Just need a truckload of Vicodin.

24
00:01:32,177 --> 00:01:34,095
- Whereas this guy...
- He's brain dead.

25
00:01:34,220 --> 00:01:35,263
No, I'm not!

26
00:01:35,388 --> 00:01:36,931
So drop it.

27
00:01:37,056 --> 00:01:38,433
See that?

28
00:01:38,558 --> 00:01:40,643
Minimal brain waves
don't mean he's alive.

29
00:01:40,769 --> 00:01:43,354
I am alive. I'm here.

30
00:01:43,521 --> 00:01:45,190
No EEG response to painful stimuli,
hot or cold.

31
00:01:45,356 --> 00:01:47,442
What you're seeing
is random, barely discernable.

32
00:01:47,567 --> 00:01:48,401
I discerned it.

33
00:01:48,526 --> 00:01:49,569
Listen to him. Please.

34
00:01:49,694 --> 00:01:52,030
No. That's just the amplifier's
internal noise level.

35
00:01:52,197 --> 00:01:53,397
It's on increased sensitivity.

36
00:01:53,448 --> 00:01:55,533
No, no, no, it's not! It's me.

37
00:01:55,658 --> 00:01:57,035
Then why is
his eye following you?

38
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:57,994
Exactly.

39
00:01:58,119 --> 00:02:00,079
Following motion is
an involuntary reflex.

40
00:02:00,205 --> 00:02:01,039
No.

41
00:02:01,164 --> 00:02:02,040
You're a doctor,

42
00:02:02,165 --> 00:02:03,416
you should know these things.

43
00:02:03,541 --> 00:02:07,378
No, no. I'm not dead.
I need help. I'm here.

44
00:02:09,464 --> 00:02:12,342
I also know about
locked-in syndrome.

45
00:02:12,884 --> 00:02:18,139
And things are either
involuntary or voluntary.

46
00:02:20,350 --> 00:02:21,851
Blink if you can hear me.

47
00:02:21,976 --> 00:02:23,520
I hear you.

48
00:02:25,021 --> 00:02:27,106
Oh. This is gonna be fun.

49
00:03:05,770 --> 00:03:07,689
Eye movement is deliberate.

50
00:03:08,523 --> 00:03:11,776
Can you blink once
for yes, twice for no?

51
00:03:11,901 --> 00:03:13,027
I hope so.

52
00:03:13,736 --> 00:03:15,572
Square root of nine?

53
00:03:19,158 --> 00:03:22,912
He got that faster than you.
Brain is fully functional.

54
00:03:23,037 --> 00:03:24,414
Where's Molly?

55
00:03:24,539 --> 00:03:25,915
You were in an accident.

56
00:03:29,836 --> 00:03:32,380
Lee, hit the brake.
Hit the brake. Hit the brake.

57
00:03:33,214 --> 00:03:36,050
You sustained a traumatic injury
to your brain stem,

58
00:03:36,175 --> 00:03:37,655
which has cut off
your brain's ability

59
00:03:37,677 --> 00:03:39,178
to communicate with
the rest of your body.

60
00:03:39,304 --> 00:03:41,723
Can you fix me? Where's Molly?

61
00:03:41,848 --> 00:03:43,766
You still have
movement in your eyes,

62
00:03:43,892 --> 00:03:45,518
so we can get you
to a rehab facility

63
00:03:45,643 --> 00:03:47,061
where they can teach you
how to communicate.

64
00:03:47,186 --> 00:03:49,647
No, I can't be stuck like this.

65
00:03:49,772 --> 00:03:53,568
Unless the crash didn't cause
the brain damage.

66
00:03:54,152 --> 00:03:56,696
Maybe the brain
damage caused the crash.

67
00:03:56,821 --> 00:04:00,992
Yeah. I couldn't stop.
Why couldn't I stop?

68
00:04:01,117 --> 00:04:03,620
Look at his palms. No scrapes.

69
00:04:05,914 --> 00:04:08,833
He didn't even try
to protect himself.

70
00:04:08,958 --> 00:04:11,294
Suggests slowed
reflexes or no reflexes.

71
00:04:11,419 --> 00:04:13,922
You're not a doctor in this hospital,
you are a patient.

72
00:04:14,047 --> 00:04:16,591
Yeah. And you're the guy
who wants to cut out my organs

73
00:04:16,716 --> 00:04:17,876
and he's the guy who doesn't.

74
00:04:17,967 --> 00:04:18,968
Stroke, cancer,

75
00:04:19,093 --> 00:04:22,764
even a simple infection, anything that
insults the central pons could do this.

76
00:04:22,889 --> 00:04:24,169
Then that means
I could be fixed.

77
00:04:24,223 --> 00:04:25,767
You're giving him false hope.

78
00:04:25,892 --> 00:04:28,603
He needs to accept
what's happened

79
00:04:28,728 --> 00:04:30,772
and work on making
the most of it.

80
00:04:40,865 --> 00:04:42,200
Molly.

81
00:04:42,325 --> 00:04:43,534
Hey.

82
00:04:44,744 --> 00:04:47,830
Don't look at me like that.
That's not making me feel better.

83
00:04:49,290 --> 00:04:50,625
I love you.

84
00:04:51,793 --> 00:04:55,463
I don't know how God is gonna get us
through this, but he will.

85
00:04:55,588 --> 00:04:57,632
Stop it, I'm blushing.

86
00:04:57,882 --> 00:04:59,258
What are you doing?

87
00:04:59,384 --> 00:05:02,470
Just looking for
some reading material for the crapper.

88
00:05:02,595 --> 00:05:05,848
- These CTs...
- Get back in your bed. Come on.

89
00:05:05,974 --> 00:05:08,476
The children are in the waiting area.
Can I bring them in?

90
00:05:08,601 --> 00:05:10,645
No. No, don't.

91
00:05:10,770 --> 00:05:12,355
You don't wanna see them?

92
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,940
I don't want them having
nightmares.

93
00:05:14,065 --> 00:05:15,566
I don't wanna scare them, Molly.

94
00:05:15,692 --> 00:05:17,485
You don't want them to see you?

95
00:05:20,738 --> 00:05:22,907
It's okay. I understand.

96
00:05:24,742 --> 00:05:26,536
You're gonna be
better soon enough.

97
00:05:27,078 --> 00:05:28,913
You really that sure?

98
00:05:29,497 --> 00:05:31,958
Why are you so sure, babe?
How do you get so sure?

99
00:05:38,798 --> 00:05:40,258
Are you okay?

100
00:05:40,383 --> 00:05:41,426
Never better.

101
00:05:41,551 --> 00:05:42,510
Here's your burger.

102
00:05:45,388 --> 00:05:49,726
If you can't bring Mohammed to
Princeton, bring Princeton to Mohammed.

103
00:05:49,851 --> 00:05:52,311
It's my diagnostics posse.

104
00:05:52,437 --> 00:05:54,188
Hot, dark and darker.

105
00:05:54,313 --> 00:05:55,940
Talk about getting
me better, please.

106
00:05:56,065 --> 00:05:57,066
What are you doing
up in Middletown?

107
00:05:57,191 --> 00:05:58,026
Who cares?

108
00:05:58,151 --> 00:06:00,820
Buying a Gibson '57 Goldtop.

109
00:06:00,945 --> 00:06:03,072
It's the guitar Duane
Allman used to play.

110
00:06:03,197 --> 00:06:05,366
Next to the trauma,
the most likely causes of

111
00:06:05,491 --> 00:06:07,618
a sudden onset of
locked-in syndrome

112
00:06:07,744 --> 00:06:09,585
are basilar artery stroke
and brain hemorrhage.

113
00:06:09,704 --> 00:06:10,788
CT was clean.

114
00:06:10,913 --> 00:06:11,994
Man, those fries look good.

115
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:12,874
Certain circulatory diseases.

116
00:06:12,999 --> 00:06:15,501
Guy's an active bike
rider, his heart's fine.

117
00:06:15,626 --> 00:06:17,378
A well-placed tumor
could explain it.

118
00:06:17,503 --> 00:06:20,798
Jeez, is the last thing I ate
gonna be the last thing I ate?

119
00:06:20,923 --> 00:06:24,177
It could evade the CT, and still show up
on an MRI with contrast.

120
00:06:24,302 --> 00:06:26,095
It was a melted PowerBar.

121
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:27,305
She's the smart one.

122
00:06:27,430 --> 00:06:29,849
I just keep dark and darker
to fill out the quota.

123
00:06:30,850 --> 00:06:34,812
If we find it, treat it,
you can be fine.

124
00:06:35,897 --> 00:06:37,982
I never thought
I'd be praying for a brain tumor,

125
00:06:38,107 --> 00:06:39,776
but please, dear God.

126
00:06:40,860 --> 00:06:43,905
If you're praying
in there, stop it right now.

127
00:06:44,030 --> 00:06:45,656
We'll get his doctor
to order an MRI.

128
00:06:45,782 --> 00:06:46,982
His doctor's busy teaching him

129
00:06:47,033 --> 00:06:49,619
how to blink out "kill me"
in Morse code.

130
00:06:50,328 --> 00:06:54,082
Luckily, I found some
forms under the mattress.

131
00:06:58,127 --> 00:07:00,922
Check it out,
they have those MRI video goggles.

132
00:07:01,047 --> 00:07:03,925
- I heard these were awesome.
- What do you see?

133
00:07:04,050 --> 00:07:05,343
It's a beach.

134
00:07:05,885 --> 00:07:07,887
Oh, look. There's Taub.

135
00:07:08,012 --> 00:07:11,933
Drinking a margarita and mocking us
for driving all the way up here

136
00:07:12,058 --> 00:07:14,685
because House said "jump."
Easy. I can still feel in here.

137
00:07:14,852 --> 00:07:18,356
Excuse Dr. Kutner. He gets a little
excited about new technology.

138
00:07:18,481 --> 00:07:21,317
It can get loud in there,
and a little closed off.

139
00:07:21,442 --> 00:07:23,945
These will put you
in a quiet place.

140
00:07:24,070 --> 00:07:26,614
You can create
a relaxing scenario for yourself.

141
00:07:26,739 --> 00:07:29,659
I hope they work.

142
00:07:29,784 --> 00:07:30,993
Wow.

143
00:07:38,876 --> 00:07:41,504
You're in my relaxing scenario?

144
00:07:42,922 --> 00:07:44,215
I guess you like me.

145
00:07:45,508 --> 00:07:47,844
Either that or
you got sent here.

146
00:07:47,969 --> 00:07:49,720
What, by God?

147
00:07:49,846 --> 00:07:52,390
I'm not sure if
I believe in God.

148
00:07:52,515 --> 00:07:55,643
You spend an awful lot of time in church
for someone who doesn't.

149
00:07:57,478 --> 00:07:59,230
I don't not believe either.

150
00:08:00,106 --> 00:08:02,316
It's either one or the other.

151
00:08:02,441 --> 00:08:05,194
I go to church mainly to
keep my wife happy, but...

152
00:08:06,821 --> 00:08:08,114
I don't know.
I've never actually thought that

153
00:08:08,239 --> 00:08:10,700
God could reach out
and affect my life.

154
00:08:10,825 --> 00:08:15,663
But getting a brilliant
doctor in the bed next to me...

155
00:08:15,788 --> 00:08:19,709
God is also the guy who opened his car
door in front of you.

156
00:08:19,834 --> 00:08:21,210
I think Molly was right.

157
00:08:21,544 --> 00:08:24,005
I think you were sent here
to make me get better.

158
00:08:25,506 --> 00:08:26,465
I think so.

159
00:08:32,513 --> 00:08:33,639
Hey.

160
00:08:35,391 --> 00:08:37,768
Hey, Dad. Making a volcano.

161
00:08:37,894 --> 00:08:41,105
Yeah. You're making a volcano. Looks
like it. What you doing, baby?

162
00:08:45,735 --> 00:08:47,320
What time is it?

163
00:08:47,445 --> 00:08:51,407
Hope you don't mind.
My new roommate snores.

164
00:08:51,532 --> 00:08:55,203
And my new room
doesn't have you.

165
00:08:56,621 --> 00:09:00,208
Your MRI showed
a lesion in the central pons.

166
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:02,001
What is that?
What does that mean?

167
00:09:02,126 --> 00:09:03,169
See it there?

168
00:09:03,294 --> 00:09:04,128
No.

169
00:09:06,589 --> 00:09:08,090
Yeah, that's what they said.

170
00:09:09,217 --> 00:09:13,262
But it's there, which means no way
head trauma did this.

171
00:09:13,679 --> 00:09:17,475
It's cancer, causing a
paraneoplastic syndrome.

172
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:19,685
Unfortunately, your
current doctor thinks

173
00:09:19,810 --> 00:09:22,813
its diffused nature
means an infection.

174
00:09:22,939 --> 00:09:25,608
Now, the bad news
is the antivirals

175
00:09:25,733 --> 00:09:28,653
he's got you on might kill you.

176
00:09:28,778 --> 00:09:29,737
I'm not gonna die.

177
00:09:29,862 --> 00:09:33,282
The good news is,
if they just almost kill you,

178
00:09:33,407 --> 00:09:37,578
then Dr. Idiot will realize that
his name is not a coincidence,

179
00:09:37,703 --> 00:09:39,497
and he'll let me
do whatever I want.

180
00:09:39,622 --> 00:09:40,539
Thank you.

181
00:09:44,126 --> 00:09:45,836
See, the irony here is,

182
00:09:47,588 --> 00:09:49,298
you're kind of fascinating.

183
00:09:50,591 --> 00:09:52,385
So many questions.

184
00:09:53,261 --> 00:09:54,929
But if you could
answer any of them,

185
00:09:55,054 --> 00:09:56,597
then you wouldn't
be fascinating.

186
00:09:56,722 --> 00:09:59,725
I get it. You're a little
nuts, aren't you?

187
00:10:03,396 --> 00:10:05,773
Your wife is the one
getting you through this.

188
00:10:05,898 --> 00:10:07,733
Your wife and me.

189
00:10:09,694 --> 00:10:12,238
Although, frankly, the MRI
was a lot more useful

190
00:10:12,363 --> 00:10:14,365
than four hours of hand holding.

191
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:17,326
I think.

192
00:10:18,411 --> 00:10:20,538
If he had a wife,
he'd know it matters.

193
00:10:21,706 --> 00:10:25,001
You're a good guy.
Easy to talk to.

194
00:10:25,126 --> 00:10:29,297
Wait, something's
happening. What's happening to me?

195
00:10:29,422 --> 00:10:31,549
Need some help in here.

196
00:10:31,674 --> 00:10:33,551
Your patient is seizing.

197
00:10:36,220 --> 00:10:37,722
Why would he have a seizure?

198
00:10:37,847 --> 00:10:39,265
Because he has cancer.

199
00:10:39,390 --> 00:10:40,590
His brain stem is compromised.

200
00:10:40,683 --> 00:10:43,227
Why are you still arguing with
this guy? You thought I was dead.

201
00:10:43,352 --> 00:10:45,563
Welcome back.
And nicely played.

202
00:10:45,688 --> 00:10:49,483
You almost died,
exactly as we planned.

203
00:10:49,608 --> 00:10:50,901
You knew this was gonna happen?

204
00:10:51,027 --> 00:10:54,572
Usually happens when you treat cancer
by pretending it's not cancer.

205
00:10:54,697 --> 00:10:57,450
- Right, Doctor? My turn?
- It's cancer?

206
00:10:57,575 --> 00:10:58,534
- No, it isn't.
- Yes.

207
00:10:58,659 --> 00:11:01,746
Small tumor in his brain stem
causing paraneoplastic syndrome.

208
00:11:01,871 --> 00:11:04,665
- He needs plasmapheresis.
- Can you give that to him?

209
00:11:04,790 --> 00:11:06,834
No, no, I'm sorry. I completely disagree
with Dr. House.

210
00:11:06,959 --> 00:11:07,918
Please shut up!

211
00:11:08,044 --> 00:11:09,211
I don't.

212
00:11:09,337 --> 00:11:11,464
Which means I can treat him.

213
00:11:11,589 --> 00:11:13,341
Let him. Let him.

214
00:11:13,466 --> 00:11:14,800
Is that what you want?

215
00:11:14,925 --> 00:11:16,469
Absolutely.

216
00:11:18,012 --> 00:11:20,056
Could you send up
a couple of bellboys?

217
00:11:30,649 --> 00:11:34,320
I got the transfer papers,
plasmapheresis is all set up.

218
00:11:34,445 --> 00:11:35,446
Are you okay?

219
00:11:35,571 --> 00:11:38,324
Fresh infusion of
macho. You like?

220
00:11:38,449 --> 00:11:41,452
I can't move, and she's worried
about his boo-boo?

221
00:11:41,577 --> 00:11:43,037
What were you
doing up there anyway?

222
00:11:43,162 --> 00:11:44,580
Antiquing.

223
00:11:44,705 --> 00:11:46,415
Found you a late
Victorian corset.

224
00:11:46,540 --> 00:11:47,833
Come by later. I'll tie you up.

225
00:11:47,958 --> 00:11:52,046
He hitting on her? If she turns
around, she's into him, too.

226
00:11:52,171 --> 00:11:53,381
And there you have it.

227
00:11:53,506 --> 00:11:55,549
Sorry, I didn't show up
in Middletown. I didn't get the message.

228
00:11:55,674 --> 00:11:57,510
Probably 'cause
there was no message.

229
00:11:57,635 --> 00:12:00,096
I decided to accept
your resignation.

230
00:12:00,221 --> 00:12:02,681
Uh, I thought we were past this.
I decided to stay.

231
00:12:02,807 --> 00:12:04,725
No, you didn't, you had it
decided for you.

232
00:12:04,850 --> 00:12:06,310
So now you're stuck here
with a boss

233
00:12:06,435 --> 00:12:08,312
who knows that you wanna be
somewhere else.

234
00:12:08,437 --> 00:12:10,314
Which means you're
no longer motivated to impress me.

235
00:12:10,439 --> 00:12:13,359
Which means you're no longer motivated
to come up with good ideas.

236
00:12:13,484 --> 00:12:14,902
Unless I'm wrong.

237
00:12:15,653 --> 00:12:18,864
Save the cheerleader,
save your world.

238
00:12:20,157 --> 00:12:20,991
I got it from here.

239
00:12:21,117 --> 00:12:22,493
I thought you
already solved this.

240
00:12:22,618 --> 00:12:24,912
You thinking you might be wrong?

241
00:12:25,037 --> 00:12:26,539
What's going on?

242
00:12:26,664 --> 00:12:29,583
Hey, just curious.

243
00:12:29,708 --> 00:12:31,877
What're you driving
up to Middletown for?

244
00:12:32,002 --> 00:12:32,837
Why do you care?

245
00:12:32,962 --> 00:12:33,921
Why does he care?

246
00:12:34,046 --> 00:12:35,423
Because I'm your friend.

247
00:12:35,548 --> 00:12:37,591
- I was buying a guitar.
- Yeah. I heard that.

248
00:12:37,716 --> 00:12:40,970
Used to belong to a guitarist who died
in a motorcycle accident.

249
00:12:41,095 --> 00:12:43,681
Just reeks of you
screwing with people.

250
00:12:43,806 --> 00:12:48,227
Your crash was 10 miles from the Orange
County Progressive Pain Clinic.

251
00:12:48,352 --> 00:12:50,396
You live 10 miles
from Mary's Dress Shop.

252
00:12:50,521 --> 00:12:52,322
And yet,
that's not even on my list of reasons

